## Deployment Options

### Option 1: GitHub Pages (Recommended — Free)

1. Create a new GitHub repository (e.g. `payments-website`)
2. Push these files to the `main` branch:
   ```bash
   git init
   git add .
   git commit -m "Initial deploy"
   git branch -M main
   git remote add origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/payments-website.git
   git push -u origin main
   ```
3. Go to **Settings → Pages → Source**: select `main` branch, root `/`
4. GitHub Pages will automatically use the `CNAME` file for your custom domain

### Option 2: Netlify Drop (Fastest)

1. Go to [netlify.com/drop](https://app.netlify.com/drop)
2. Drag and drop the `payments-website` folder
3. Set custom domain to `payments.ebiya.sg` in site settings

### Option 3: Any Static Host

Upload `index.html` and `CNAME` to any web server or CDN (Cloudflare Pages, Vercel, AWS S3 + CloudFront, etc.)

---

## DNS Configuration

Add this DNS record at your domain registrar (where `ebiya.sg` is managed):

| Type  | Name       | Value                            |
| ----- | ---------- | -------------------------------- |
| CNAME | `payments` | `YOUR_GITHUB_USERNAME.github.io` |

Or for Netlify/Vercel, point the CNAME to your deployment URL.

**Allow 24–48 hours for DNS propagation.**

